Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%oz} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve, peel, and cut @shallot{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and quarter @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces. Finely chop @sun-dried tomatoes{1.5%oz}. Roughly chop @parsley{¼%oz}.

Toss broccoli and shallot on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. (Be sure to measure the Italian Seasoning.)

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

While pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add zucchini and @garlic powder{1%tsp}; cook, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is lightly browned and softened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add sun-dried tomatoes and cook, stirring frequently, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Stir @crushed tomatoes{13.76%units}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1%unit}, ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water, @sugar{1%tsp}, and a pinch of salt and pepper into pan with zucchini. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until flavors meld, ~{1-3%minutes}.

Add drained penne and a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} to pan with sauce. Toss to combine; season with salt and pepper to taste.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is thoroughly coated in sauce.

Divide pasta between bowls. Top with broccoli and shallot. Garnish with parsley and serve.